Title: CSRF Protection
Question: Which cookie attribute helps prevent Cross-Site Request Forgery (CSRF) attacks?
A. HttpOnly
B. SameSite
C. Secure
D. Domain

Correct Answer: B
Explanation: The SameSite attribute restricts when cookies are sent with cross-site requests, helping to prevent CSRF attacks. When set to "Strict", cookies are only sent in a first-party context.
